Let's take a look at the second floor.

17:42.979 --> 17:45.147
We're known for our service.

17:45.231 --> 17:46.940
That's gotta be a tough job.

17:47.024 --> 17:49.025
I know.

17:49.110 --> 17:51.945
I've always liked how quiet it is up here.

17:52.029 --> 17:54.948
Well, that might explain the lack of customers.

17:56.492 --> 17:59.786
I can see the charm , but. . .

17:59.871 --> 18:02.831
the room is too dark, too old-fashioned .

18:02.915 --> 18:04.124
The products look old .

18:04.208 --> 18:05.584
But the people look wonderful .

18:07.420 --> 18:09.963
It's a shame we're gonna
have to lop their heads off.

18:10.047 --> 18:12.340
It'll ruin your favorite part of the store.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.634
It's not my favorite part, actually.

18:30.568 --> 18:32.360
The grand lot of us are going to Lansky's.

18:32.445 --> 18:34.029
Can you believe it?

18:34.113 --> 18:36.656
Have a swell time. I've got plans.

18:40.036 --> 18:41.620
You look nice.

18:55.301 --> 18:56.510
Hell .

18:56.594 --> 18:59.304
Manhattan at your feet,
I can see the appeal.

18:59.388 --> 19:01.014
The view's okay.

19:01.098 --> 19:04.810
No, this is my favorite part of the store.

19:06.103 --> 19:07.687
Hey there, Missy.

19:08.981 --> 19:10.816
Hey.

19:10.900 --> 19:12.818
I haven't seen you in a while.

19:12.902 --> 19:15.403
- Hey.
- How did they get the penthouse?

19:15.488 --> 19:17.072
They patrol .

19:17.156 --> 19:18.907
It's the only way to make sure

19:18.991 --> 19:20.909
there isn't anyone hiding
in the store at night.

19:20.993 --> 19:22.619
Well, they know I'm with you , right?

19:22.703 --> 19:25.914
These two are Carla and Leona.

19:25.998 --> 19:29.334
Not the originals, but third generation,

19:29.418 --> 19:31.962
and what every generation
of Menken dog

19:32.046 --> 19:36.049
shall be named until the end of time.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.051
I made my father's
legal counsel add that

19:38.135 --> 19:40.053
to the store's by-laws when I was 9.

19:40.137 --> 19:42.639
So even then you enjoyed
telling men what to do.

19:42.723 --> 19:46.101
To be fair, the store
was practically home.

19:46.185 --> 19:48.478
My father liked to work.

19:48.563 --> 19:50.981
I used to come out here
and talk to them--

19:51.065 --> 19:52.065
well, the originals--

19:52.149 --> 19:54.067
every night.

19:54.151 --> 19:58.029
For a little girl,
a dog can be all you need .

19:58.114 --> 20:01.074
They protect you . They listen .

20:01.158 --> 20:03.577
I had my sister, but there weren't other kids.

20:03.661 --> 20:07.080
And, of course,
my mother wasn't around .

20:07.164 --> 20:09.958
Well , that's not always a bad thing .

20:10.042 --> 20:12.085
Who knows?

20:12.169 --> 20:14.170
She died when she was having me.

20:16.591 --> 20:19.551
Anyway, my sister
became my only company.

20:19.635 --> 20:21.094
And frankly,

20:21.178 --> 20:23.179
these bitches were easier to handle.

20:28.811 --> 20:30.186
What is this?

20:33.733 --> 20:36.651
Don't try to convince me
that you were ever unloved .

21:07.892 --> 21:09.476
I don't know what to say.

21:19.528 --> 21:20.779
Listen . . .

21:25.660 --> 21:27.702
I'm married .

21:34.251 --> 21:37.379
I guess I didn't ask
'cause I didn't want to know.

21:39.632 --> 21:41.549
That shouldn't have happened .

21:43.302 --> 21:45.929
Well, you couldn't help yourself.

21:46.013 --> 21:49.182
I knew what I wanted . . .

21:49.266 --> 21:51.184
from the first time
you stormed out of our office.

21:51.268 --> 21:53.269
You stormed out of your office.

21:55.106 --> 21:58.108
I took you up here. That was stupid .

21:59.819 --> 22:01.861
I just so looked forward
to seeing you again .

22:03.906 --> 22:05.657
Now I guess that's over.

22:17.712 --> 22:19.087
I know you understand

22:19.171 --> 22:22.298
I'd rather not have to
explain this to anyone.

22:22.383 --> 22:23.425
The account stays.

22:23.509 --> 22:25.510
I just want someone else on it.

22:27.888 --> 22:30.348
Don't look at me like that.

22:31.600 --> 22:33.643
What do you do,
just kiss women all the time?

22:33.728 --> 22:34.853
Women you aren't married to?

22:34.937 --> 22:36.896
Of course not.

22:36.981 --> 22:40.316
Well, then, am I supposed to live
some life running alongside yours?

22:48.325 --> 22:51.327
I have some checks to sign.

23:36.207 --> 23:37.957
Excuse me.

23:38.042 --> 23:39.751
You dropped your paper.

23:43.297 --> 23:44.380
Thank you .

24:20.417 --> 24:21.376
Daddy!

24:21.460 --> 24:23.169
Daddy! Daddy!

24:23.254 --> 24:25.255
Wake up. It's my birthday.

24:25.339 --> 24:28.258
It's my birthday!

24:28.342 --> 24:31.052
It's not your birthday. It's your party.

24:31.137 --> 24:32.345
Don, the party's at 2:00.

24:32.429 --> 24:35.932
You have to put together
the P-L-A-Y-H-O-U-S-E.

24:37.226 --> 24:39.269
How am I going to put together a pony?

24:39.353 --> 24:42.313
A pony? I'm getting a pony?

24:42.398 --> 24:44.440
Bobby, I'm getting a pony!

24:46.026 --> 24:47.652
Great.

24:49.029 --> 24:51.364
She'll forget all about it
when she sees the playhouse.

24:55.786 --> 24:58.454
There's a bacon and egg sandwich
for you on the range.

25:47.546 --> 25:49.547
It's got a red door like ours!

25:49.632 --> 25:51.341
Daddy!

25:51.425 --> 25:53.760
You are not supposed to see this yet.

25:54.929 --> 25:57.472
Why don't you run to the garage
and get me another beer?

25:57.556 --> 25:58.681
Okay.

26:05.564 --> 26:06.689
Capers?

26:06.774 --> 26:08.483
You want to pick those out of the rug?

26:08.567 --> 26:10.443
Well, they look naked .

26:10.527 --> 26:14.447
Well, the only thing
this one wants is raw hamburger.

26:14.531 --> 26:16.866
What does that mean?

26:16.951 --> 26:18.451
I think that's enough of that.

26:18.535 --> 26:19.744
Well , how many are we?

26:19.828 --> 26:21.454
Us, you--

26:21.538 --> 26:23.081
Carlton's with the kids. Make it quick.

26:23.165 --> 26:25.333
The Darlings, Helen Bishop--

26:25.417 --> 26:27.627
- You didn't.
- I had to.

26:27.711 --> 26:29.462
She saw me buying balloons at the market.

26:29.546 --> 26:31.047
- Didn't seem right.
- So what?

26:31.131 --> 26:34.133
I just brought her the pie,
got my dish back at the end .

26:34.218 --> 26:36.511
Have you seen her walking
up Downtree Ridge?

26:36.595 --> 26:38.846
Where the hell is she walking to?

26:39.932 --> 26:42.183
I don't know.

26:42.268 --> 26:43.476
How old is her kid?

26:43.560 --> 26:45.603
Kids.

26:45.688 --> 26:46.896
The boy is 9.

26:46.981 --> 26:48.898
I'm gonna say Gary, maybe Glen?

26:48.983 --> 26:50.483
And the baby is a 2-year-old .

26:50.567 --> 26:52.527
She said she was gonna
try and get a sitter.

26:52.611 --> 26:54.654
I would .

26:54.738 --> 26:56.781
It's probably a big event for her.

27:03.747 --> 27:05.498
That man .

27:07.459 --> 27:08.626
I know.

28:02.056 --> 28:05.224
You didn't use the powder room , did you?

28:05.309 --> 28:07.185
It will appear untouched .

28:08.520 --> 28:09.562
Everyone's gonna be here soon .

28:09.646 --> 28:11.564
Why don't you go up
and take a shower?

28:11.648 --> 28:13.316
Want company?

28:57.277 --> 28:59.737
Mint juleps. It's that time of year.

28:59.822 --> 29:02.698
- Wonderful.
- I'm so thirsty lately.

29:05.702 --> 29:07.412
Ready or not, here I come!

29:07.496 --> 29:09.956
There's date nut bread,
cold turkey,

29:10.040 --> 29:12.166
and Waldorf salad for the adults.

29:16.088 --> 29:18.256
And I just made
peanut butter sandwiches for the kids.

29:18.340 --> 29:20.049
I know everybody eats that.

29:20.134 --> 29:21.759
Thank you .

29:21.844 --> 29:23.761
And in case anybody's going to ask,

29:23.846 --> 29:25.346
I did not get that clown .

29:25.431 --> 29:26.681
- Oh .
- Oh .

29:26.765 --> 29:28.724
He got booked in some off-Broadway show.

29:28.809 --> 29:30.810
About clowns? I think we saw that.

29:30.894 --> 29:34.147
It's not the one
where they take their clothes off, is it?

29:34.231 --> 29:35.273
Who knew that could be boring?

29:37.317 --> 29:39.444
Want something a little
stronger there, Carlton?

29:39.528 --> 29:40.653
He'll manage.

29:40.737 --> 29:42.155
We were thinking about you , Don .

29:43.740 --> 29:45.241
We saw this thing on TV.

29:45.325 --> 29:47.660
It was right in the middle
of the news. It was cute.

29:47.744 --> 29:48.911
The guy flying with his hat on.

29:48.996 --> 29:51.247
- Did you do that one?
- It was so cute.

29:51.373 --> 29:54.584
- I think the man looks exactly like Henry.
- Except not as handsome.

29:55.669 --> 29:57.170
I haven't seen that.

29:57.254 --> 29:59.672
I'm going to go and lay
the kids' food out.

29:59.756 --> 30:01.924
Let's not even bother
trying to get them to sit.

30:02.009 --> 30:03.301
I'll co-pilot.

30:03.385 --> 30:04.927
Heard a good one the other day.

30:05.012 --> 30:05.928
No, Chet.

30:06.013 --> 30:07.430
I'm gonna tell the joke.

30:07.514 --> 30:09.682
Your wife and your lawyer
are drowning .

30:09.766 --> 30:11.225
You have a choice to make:

30:11.310 --> 30:13.686
you go to lunch or a movie?

30:13.770 --> 30:15.188
It's good, right?

30:15.272 --> 30:16.689
Hey, I'm missing the ball game.

30:16.773 --> 30:18.316
I might as well have some fun .

30:18.400 --> 30:19.859
Hey.

30:19.943 --> 30:21.944
So how are things on Mad Ave, Don?

30:22.029 --> 30:24.238
Looks like they're taking care of you .

30:24.323 --> 30:26.949
We got it all, huh?

30:27.034 --> 30:28.826
Yep, this is it.

30:31.663 --> 30:35.875
Maybe it's his obsession with sports,
but it's been hard for Jack.

30:35.959 --> 30:38.920
Marilyn, I've been watching Kevin,
and he gets around very well.

30:40.797 --> 30:43.299
I bet he doesn't know the difference.

30:43.383 --> 30:44.717
He does.

30:44.801 --> 30:46.719
He's very determined .

30:46.803 --> 30:49.764
Jack really gets angry anytime someone
mentions the vaccine,

30:49.848 --> 30:51.807
and I tell him we should be grateful .

30:51.892 --> 30:54.018
First of all, it could
have been much worse.

30:54.102 --> 30:55.728
It could have gotten to his lungs.

30:55.812 --> 30:58.523
Second of all, this can't happen
to other children .

30:58.607 --> 31:00.399
They think they're athletes.

31:00.484 --> 31:01.776
I want to say to Chet,

31:01.860 --> 31:04.111
"I saw you play football in high school.

31:04.196 --> 31:07.323
Your son's going to be
a tackling dummy just like you ."

31:17.918 --> 31:19.043
According to Glen here,

31:19.127 --> 31:22.421
when the door's a little bit open,
you're supposed to come in .

31:22.506 --> 31:24.423
Hello, Helen .

31:26.093 --> 31:30.221
I hate to start with a bunch of excuses,
but the babysitter was late,

31:30.305 --> 31:32.139
and I still haven't
unpacked all the boxes,

31:32.224 --> 31:34.559
so this was the only paper I could find .

31:36.103 --> 31:39.855
It should be Christmas all year
as far as I'm concerned .

31:43.860 --> 31:46.404
A jury in New York City

31:46.488 --> 31:47.863
is expected to receive
the tax evasion paper--

31:49.324 --> 31:53.327
. . .Opera's production
of Mozart's Marriage of Figaro,

31:53.412 --> 31:56.747
with Robert Merrill and Joan Sutherland .

31:56.832 --> 31:59.125
Don, you have to pick up the cake
from H ightop.

31:59.209 --> 32:02.712
Oh , and this is Helen Bishop and Glen .

32:02.796 --> 32:03.879
Nice to meet you all .

32:05.674 --> 32:07.592
Don . He goes with me.

32:07.676 --> 32:10.678
Then Carlton, Chet, and Jack.

32:10.762 --> 32:11.804
Glen , I'm pretty sure there are

32:11.888 --> 32:13.222
some peanut butter
sandwiches and a BB gun

32:13.307 --> 32:14.265
out there in the backyard .

32:14.349 --> 32:15.891
Why don't you come with me?

32:21.982 --> 32:23.774
Don, can I speak with you?

32:23.859 --> 32:26.819
Let's see, I told you about the cake,

32:26.903 --> 32:29.822
and-- oh, can you take
some movies this time?

32:29.906 --> 32:32.617
Of everyone or just Chief Tiny Tim?

32:32.701 --> 32:35.828
You bought that camera,
and you always forget.

32:35.912 --> 32:37.371
Okay.

32:41.877 --> 32:45.838
Ladies, ladies, this is Helen Bishop.

32:45.922 --> 32:47.840
- This is Marilyn .
- Nice to meet you .

32:47.924 --> 32:48.841
And Nancy.

32:48.925 --> 32:51.093
She seems scared , poor thing .

32:51.178 --> 32:55.181
Trust me, those hens are
gonna peck her to death .

32:55.265 --> 32:57.933
Do you see her running around
in that little Volkswagen?

32:58.018 --> 32:59.435
That's kind of desperate.

32:59.519 --> 33:01.646
That won't help her.
It's got no back seat.

33:01.730 --> 33:03.439
She'll have to find some midget hitchhiker.

33:05.275 --> 33:08.986
Last time I saw one of those,
I think I was throwing a grenade into it.

33:09.071 --> 33:09.987
Yeah .

33:10.072 --> 33:12.740
The problem with Easter break
is it's too long .

33:12.824 --> 33:13.908
The doldrums.

33:13.992 --> 33:16.869
We're thinking about seven days,
six nights, in Boca Raton,

33:16.953 --> 33:19.080
with mosquitoes as big as a silver dollar.

33:19.164 --> 33:22.541
And believe me, those aren't the only
giant noses you'll have to deal with .

33:22.626 --> 33:24.377
Francine.

33:24.461 --> 33:26.295
Carlton and I went
there on our honeymoon,

33:26.380 --> 33:28.506
and all I can say
is we were outnumbered .

33:28.590 --> 33:29.507
It's uncomfortable.

33:29.591 --> 33:30.925
You want to be able to relax.

33:31.009 --> 33:33.010
We went to Bermuda
on our honeymoon.

33:33.095 --> 33:34.220
Pink sand beaches.

33:35.305 --> 33:36.472
Where did you go?

33:37.724 --> 33:40.393
Oh, I'm-- I'm sorry.

33:42.145 --> 33:44.980
It's okay. I went to Paris.

33:45.065 --> 33:47.900
Four years of Mount Holyoke French .

33:47.984 --> 33:49.568
Haven't used it since.

33:52.698 --> 33:55.908
And I wouldn't give it back,
even being with Glen's father.

33:55.992 --> 33:57.993
Is that your ex-husband?

33:58.995 --> 34:00.705
Yes.

34:01.998 --> 34:03.916
I went to Italy.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.209
Not on my honeymoon ,

34:05.293 --> 34:08.003
but right after I graduated from Bryn Mawr.

34:08.088 --> 34:09.380
What a summer.

34:09.464 --> 34:10.673
Three Coins in the Fountain .

34:10.757 --> 34:11.966
It was right about that time.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.926
You must have loved Paris.

34:14.010 --> 34:15.386
It's all walking .

34:15.470 --> 34:17.054
What do you mean?

34:17.139 --> 34:20.307
Just that I've seen you
walking around the neighborhood .

34:20.392 --> 34:23.978
I've seen you , too, when I was driving .
I think I waved .

34:24.062 --> 34:25.938
Where are you going
when you do that?

34:26.022 --> 34:29.024
No place. I just like to walk.

34:32.070 --> 34:33.738
But where?

34:33.822 --> 34:35.656
Anywhere.

34:35.741 --> 34:38.325
It just relaxes me and clears my mind .

34:38.410 --> 34:40.619
I heard on the radio that Einstein did it.

34:40.704 --> 34:43.205
Einstein? He's got
his hands into everything .

34:56.928 --> 34:57.970
Sweetie.

34:58.054 --> 34:59.096
H i, Daddy!

35:13.236 --> 35:14.904
What are you , Frank Sinatra?

35:14.988 --> 35:16.781
I was looking for Glen .

35:16.865 --> 35:19.784
Bunch of them just ran through .

35:23.121 --> 35:25.080
There are the boys.

35:25.165 --> 35:27.082
How are we doing?

35:31.671 --> 35:33.422
It's, uh , it's Helen, right?

35:35.801 --> 35:38.010
I know your situation ,

35:38.094 --> 35:40.262
and my heart breaks for that little boy.

35:40.347 --> 35:42.097
I have a baby, too.

35:43.099 --> 35:44.308
You can act strong ,

35:44.392 --> 35:46.519
but I just want to volunteer.

35:46.603 --> 35:47.770
If you ever need someone

35:47.854 --> 35:49.980
to throw the ball
around with him some Sunday,

35:50.065 --> 35:51.941
take him to the beach .

35:52.025 --> 35:54.109
That would be nice.

35:55.487 --> 35:58.614
I'm sure eventually I'd get so used
to your Sunday visits,

35:58.698 --> 36:01.700
I'd join you at the beach,
just the four of us.

36:01.785 --> 36:04.787
Then one night, you'd
drop us off at the house

36:04.871 --> 36:07.540
and walk me in with an umbrella.

36:07.624 --> 36:09.041
The kids would go to sleep,

36:09.125 --> 36:11.001
and we'd laugh
about all the funny things

36:11.086 --> 36:12.753
that happened at the beach that day.

36:12.838 --> 36:15.047
I don't want you telling Francine

36:15.131 --> 36:17.716
that I suggested
something that I didn't.

36:17.801 --> 36:21.053
Well, I'm sorry if I misunderstood .

37:05.223 --> 37:07.099
You dented the car.

37:07.183 --> 37:10.102
I like sleeping on the couch .

37:10.186 --> 37:11.896
I don't like your tone.

37:11.980 --> 37:14.189
Take your shoes off.

37:31.249 --> 37:33.250
Interesting crowd in there.

37:36.922 --> 37:38.881
Same crowd out here.

37:40.258 --> 37:42.509
How about the Einstein thing?

37:42.594 --> 37:45.721
I wonder if old Albert swung his hips
like that when he walked .

37:45.805 --> 37:48.140
She probably got
her hair tips from him , too.

37:48.224 --> 37:49.850
Glen is so quiet.

37:49.935 --> 37:51.518
Not to mention wrinkled .

37:51.603 --> 37:55.356
Maybe she hasn't unpacked
her iron, either.

37:55.440 --> 37:58.609
Christmas paper? Please.

37:58.693 --> 38:00.152
She works.

38:00.236 --> 38:03.155
It has to be hard to run a house, too.

38:03.239 --> 38:05.491
Manning a counter
at a jewelry store?

38:05.575 --> 38:07.159
It's not that demanding.

38:07.243 --> 38:11.163
I don't know. I had a job in sales
before I was a mom .

38:11.247 --> 38:13.165
Have you seen my mom?

38:13.249 --> 38:16.919
No, honey, Maybe she's
in the dining room .

38:19.381 --> 38:20.673
Betty.

38:20.757 --> 38:21.840
What?

38:34.479 --> 38:37.272
Don , will you please go
to Hightop and get the cake?

38:48.952 --> 38:51.870
Hey. Don't run in the house.

38:51.955 --> 38:53.205
What is going on in here?

38:53.289 --> 38:55.332
Your kid knocked over a drink.

38:55.417 --> 38:58.585
You need to tell him
this is not a jungle gym .

38:58.670 --> 39:01.839
Ernie, did you hear what Mr. Farrelly said?

39:03.091 --> 39:06.010
Did you say you were sorry?

39:06.094 --> 39:07.803
Do you want some more?

39:07.887 --> 39:10.597
No. Come on . He heard me.

39:10.682 --> 39:13.726
Go get your mother
and have her clean this up.

39:52.348 --> 39:53.974
Okay. Thank you .

39:57.353 --> 39:58.687
The woman at the bakery said

39:58.772 --> 40:00.898
he picked up the cake
almost an hour ago.

40:00.982 --> 40:03.150
Do you think he had an accident?

40:03.234 --> 40:04.276
Let's go.

40:04.360 --> 40:06.153
We haven't done birthday cake.

40:06.237 --> 40:07.738
There's not going to be a cake.

40:07.822 --> 40:09.948
Am I the only one that knows that?

40:11.242 --> 40:15.496
Don Draper, you are a first class heel,
and I salute you .

40:15.580 --> 40:17.289
Let's go.

40:17.373 --> 40:19.625
Swell party. Food was delicious.

40:25.757 --> 40:28.300
I might have a cake.

40:28.384 --> 40:30.552
A Sara Lee in my freezer.

40:30.637 --> 40:32.721
Well, could you go get it?

40:32.806 --> 40:34.973
Please. That would be so great.

40:44.609 --> 40:49.613
For she's a jolly good fellow

40:49.697 --> 40:53.951
For Sally's a jolly good fellow

40:54.035 --> 41:00.833
Which nobody can deny

41:01.918 --> 41:04.253
Happy Birthday, little lady.

42:21.915 --> 42:23.332
Daddy!

42:31.174 --> 42:32.925
Mommy, Mommy, look!

